#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:4(title)
msgid "Error Handling"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:7(title)
msgid "Importance of Error Handling"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:10(p)
msgid "Decent error handling is important because:"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:16(e)
msgid "before"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:15(li)
msgid "Errors must be detected <placeholder-1/> portage tries to install a broken or incomplete package onto the live filesystem. If build failures aren't caught, a working package could be unmerged and replaced with nothing."
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:23(c)
msgid "src_compile"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:20(li)
msgid "When receiving bug reports, it is a lot easier to figure out what went wrong if you know exactly which call caused the error, rather than just knowing that, say, something somewhere in <placeholder-1/> broke."
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:25(li)
msgid "Good error handling and notification can help cut down on the number of bug reports received for a package."
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:35(title)
msgid "The <c>die</c> Function"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:39(c) devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:44(c) devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:73(c) devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:77(c)
msgid "die"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:38(p)
msgid "The <placeholder-1/> function should be used to indicate a fatal error and abort the build. Its parameters should be the message to display."
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:43(p)
msgid "Although <placeholder-1/> will work with no parameters, a short message should always be provided to ease error identification. This is especially important when a function can die in multiple places."
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:51(c) devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:63(c)
msgid "|| die"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:51(c)
msgid "epatch"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:52(c)
msgid "emake"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:54(c)
msgid "ls /usr/lib*/portage/bin/ebuild-helpers"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:54(uri)
msgid "EAPI&gt;=4"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:49(p)
msgid "Some portage-provided functions will automatically die upon failure. Others will not. It is for example safe to omit the <placeholder-1/> after a call to <placeholder-2/>, but not <placeholder-3/>. The reason is that external binaries are not able to call die that is a bash function. You can see what commands are external binaries with <placeholder-4/>. In <placeholder-5/> all ebuild-helpers automatically die upon failure."
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:59(c)
msgid "eerror"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:57(p)
msgid "Sometimes displaying additional error information beforehand can be useful. Use <placeholder-1/> to do this. See <uri link=\"::ebuild-writing/messages\"/>."
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:62(p)
msgid "It's best to use <placeholder-1/> too often than too little."
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:69(title)
msgid "<c>die</c> and Subshells"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:73(b)
msgid "will not work in a subshell"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:72(warning)
msgid "<placeholder-1/><placeholder-2/>."
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:76(p)
msgid "The following code will not work as expected, since the <placeholder-1/> is inside a subshell:"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:81(codesample)
msgid "[[ -f foorc ]] &amp;&amp; ( update_foorc || die \"Couldn't update foorc!\" )"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:86(c)
msgid "if"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:85(p)
msgid "The correct way to rewrite this is to use an <placeholder-1/> block:"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:89(codesample)
msgid "if [[ -f foorc ]] ; then update_foorc || die \"Couldn't update foorc!\" fi"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:95(p)
msgid "When using pipes, a subshell is introduced, so the following is unsafe:"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:99(codesample)
msgid "cat list | while read file ; do epatch ${file} ; done"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:103(p)
msgid "Using input redirection (see <uri link=\"::tools-reference/cat/#Abuse of cat\"/>) avoids this problem:"
msgstr ""

#: devmanual/ebuild-writing/error-handling/text.xml:108(codesample)
msgid "while read file ; do epatch ${file} ; done &lt; list"
msgstr ""

